<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/carl-amery-502619.html" class="external text" title="http://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/carl-amery-502619.html" rel="nofollow">Carl Amery - Writer and eco-thinker</a> <a href="/wiki/The_Independent" title="The Independent">The Independent</a> - Obituaries, date:13 August 2005, accessed: 29 July 2008</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA6548135.html" class="external text" title="http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA6548135.html" rel="nofollow">"Master of Alternate History" by Melissa Mia Hall -- Publishers Weekly, 4/7/2008</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFSheckley1992"><a href="/wiki/Robert_Sheckley" title="Robert Sheckley">Sheckley, Robert</a> (1992). ""Dukakis and the Aliens"". <i><a href="/wiki/Alternate_Presidents" title="Alternate Presidents">Alternate Presidents</a></i> (New York: Tom Doherty Associates): 453–466. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0812511921" class="internal">ISBN 0812511921</a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC" class="mw-redirect">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/25288762" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/25288762" rel="nofollow">25288762</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%22Dukakis+and+the+Aliens%22&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BAlternate+Presidents%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Sheckley&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.au=Sheckley%2C+Robert&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.pages=453%E2%80%93466&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Tom+Doherty+Associates&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/25288762&amp;rft.isbn=0812511921&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Alternate_history"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
